sense.s:
And ADbR He spoke; (AZ, S, O, K;) as though meaning he made speech to issue: (S, O: [in both of which it is implied that it is app. from what here next precedes:]) or he spoke uninterruptedly: (TA:) or he talked loudly; as also DabRa↓ [aor.
Dabiba
]: (AA, TA in art. hDb: [but it will be seen in what follows that both of these verbs have also a contr. meaning:]) and he called out, or cried out, (K, TA,) and raised a clamour, or confused noise. (TA.) And ADbR Alqawomu The people, or party, spoke, one to another: (TA:) or spoke; and entered, or launched forth, into discourse, or were profuse therein: (AHát, TA:) or spoke all together. (Har p. 543.) And ADbR maA fiI nafosihi He uttered, or expressed, what was in his mind. (As, TA. [See also the same phrase with EalaI after the verb in what follows.])
